race.comment: PHOENIX POWER (7) not far away over this course and distance two-back, before heading to the provincials when a tiring on-pace last over 1900m at Newcastle. Comes here in peak condition and can stalk the speed with a more patient ride. No surprise to see him take this out. NAUGHTY NURSE (10) indicated she was close to her peak when attacking the line late for a game second over 1500m at Muswellbrook. Likely to go back again from the sticky draw and close strongly. WILDERNESS STAR (11) tough old mare with good figures at this track and trip. Drops further in weight with Farr's 2kg claim after disappointing when eighth over 1400m Grafton. Assess on her good third here two starts back. GOLDEN COPPER (8) bounced off her encouraging first-up fourth, with a dominant on-pace victory in good style with the 58kg over 1315m at Coffs Harbour. A repeat effort can see her win again.
